        <body>
            <p>p. Steamer.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>, <date>21st Feb
                1866</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Since writing you on <date>21st</date> ult. I<lb/> have the pleasure
                to own the receipt of your fa<lb/>vor of <date>8th</date> ult. I regret to learn
                thereby that<lb/> you had been unwell, and sincerely trust that<lb/> you have quite
                recovered, and may long enjoy<lb/> the blessing of health. <del>H</del></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Herewith I beg to <sic>inclose</sic> an obituary of<lb/> the late
                    <persName>Mrs. Petit</persName> (eldest daughter of <persName>Mr. M.<lb/> B.
                    Simmonds</persName>) <persName>Mrs. P.</persName> was a truly pious and<lb/>
                exemplary tho' retiring character, &amp; <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName><lb/> whose
                pupil she had been during the first term<lb/> of his ministry here, descanted at
                great length<lb/> on her many virtues. You will please have the<lb/> notice inserted
                in the first number of the Occi„<lb/>dent after its receipt, and send me the Bill for<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. P.</persName> immediately. For the Med. &amp; Prayers, I<lb/> have
                rec. $1.75 in specie — With due regard</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am, Rev &amp; dear Sir, Truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">D. M. Piza</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
